Experiment 1 — Git Operations (commit, branch, push, merge)
What the examiner wants

Show that you can:

create a git repository
commit a file
create a branch
merge the branch
push to remote
Step 1 — Create project folder

Open VS Code

File → Open Folder

Create a folder:

git-lab

Step 2 — Open terminal

In VS Code:

Terminal → New Terminal

You should see something like

PS C:\Users\yourname\git-lab>

Step 3 — Initialize Git

Run:

git init

This creates a hidden .git folder.

Step 4 — Create a file

Create file:

README.md

Write:

# DevOps Lab

Step 5 — Add file to git

Run:

git add README.md
Step 6 — Commit file

Run:

git commit -m "Initial commit"

Step 7 — Create branch

Run:

git checkout -b feature

Step 8 — Add another file

Create:

hello.txt

Write:

Hello from feature branch

Step 9 — Commit branch change

Run:

git add hello.txt
git commit -m "Added hello file"

Step 10 — Merge branch

Switch to main:

git checkout main

Merge:

git merge feature

Step 11 — Show history
git log --oneline
Output

You will see something like

Added hello file
Initial commit
